    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If it's only happening when you *start* moving, that points toward something momentarily engaging. The wear indicator or a sensor, perhaps one that wasn't properly seated, could be shrieking against the rotor upon initial movement. Another possibility is a slight misalignment or contamination on the new brake pads themselves. Sometimes, a tiny amount of leftover dust or manufacturing residue can cause a high-pitched sound until the bedding-in process wears it off.",
